<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="AppDiffEVT" checkit-title="Extreme Value Theorem">
    <statement>
        <p> 
Explain how to find the absolute minimum and absolute maximum values of the
function <m>f(x)=-2 \, x^{3} + 12 \, x^{2} + 30 \, x - 71</m> on the interval <m>[3,9]</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
The absolute extrema may occur at these <m>x</m>-values:
<m>3, 5, 9</m>.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><p><m>f(3)=73</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(5)=129</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(9)=-287</m></p></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
Thus the absolute minimum is <m>-287</m> and the absolute
maximum is <m>129</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
(The value <m>f(-1)=-87</m>
is ignored as <m>-1</m> isn't in the given interval.)
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
